  "prompt": "What are the career opportunities after getting PhD degree in aerospace engineering from IIT Madras?",
  "response": "After obtaining a PhD in Aerospace Engineering from IIT Madras, you have several promising career opportunities:\n\n1. Academic Careers\n- Professor/Assistant Professor in universities\n- Research Scientist in academic institutions\n- Postdoctoral Research Fellow\n- Academic Researcher\n\n2. Research Organizations\n- ISRO (Indian Space Research Organisation)\n- DRDO (Defence Research and Development Organisation)\n- National Aerospace Laboratories\n- CSIR laboratories\n- Research centers and think tanks\n\n3. Government Sectors\n- Civil Aviation Department\n- Space and Defense Research Wings\n- Ministry of Defence\n- Indian Armed Forces (Technical Roles)\n\n4. Aerospace Industry\n- Aerospace Manufacturing Companies\n- Aircraft Design and Development\n- Propulsion System Design\n- Satellite Technology\n- Companies like HAL, Boeing, Airbus, etc.\n\n5. Private Sector Opportunities\n- Aerospace R&D firms\n- Consulting organizations\n- Technology companies\n- Drone manufacturing and design\n- Robotics and Automation firms\n\n6. Entrepreneurship\n- Start your own aerospace research firm\n- Technology consultancy\n- Innovation-driven aerospace startups\n\n7. International Opportunities\n- NASA\n- European Space Agency\n- Aerospace research institutions worldwide\n\nThese opportunities depend on individual skills, specialization, and research expertise.",
